{"type":"text","timestamp":1775853589226,"sessionID":"ses_286e34833ffedub7xE6ZLTR62L","part":{"id":"prt_d791f388a001r2TZoFW9tO23x4","messageID":"msg_d791f1324001sdbH9w7Hbufi60","sessionID":"ses_286e34833ffedub7xE6ZLTR62L","type":"text","text":"## Verification Summary\n\n**Issue Found:** The spec provided (`deployment/client-go.md`) describes Kubernetes client-go code generation, but the AR title refers to \"Router JWT Authentication and Issuance\". There's a mismatch between the AR title and spec content.\n\n**Findings:**\n\n1. **No client-go implementation exists** - The spec describes a Kubernetes client-go library for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, but no `client-go/` directory exists in the project.\n\n2. **JWT implementation is complete** (`pkg/router/`):\n   - `jwt.go`: JWTManager with token generation, validation, refresh, key persistence\n   - `middleware/auth.go`: JWT authentication middleware, token issuance/refresh handlers\n   - `errors.go`: Comprehensive JWT error types (expired, missing, invalid, signing, key load)\n   - All tests pass after fixing two bugs\n\n**Fixed Bugs:**\n- `pkg/router/errors.go:68`: `JWTSigningError.Error()` didn't handle nil `Err` → Added nil check\n- `pkg/router/errors_test.go:170`: Called `Error()` on `APIStatus` interface → Cast to `error`\n- `pkg/router/jwt_test.go:375`: Type mismatch (`int` vs `int64`) → Changed to `int64(300)`\n\n**Test Results:** All tests now pass ✅\n\nThe client-go spec has **not been implemented** - would need to run `make gen-client` to generate the client-go library from `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.","time":{"start":1775853589224,"end":1775853589224}}}
